content:
I hope everyone had a great weekend. Just a reminder this is National Women's Checkup Day. Please take a moment to tell someone you love to take time for themselves and their health. 

The goal of National Women’s Checkup Day 2016 is to remind women to maintain regular checkups as one of five healthy habits they can do to improve their health.  

Whether you simply schedule a screening or an exam or go and have one today - please take care of your health. Screenings could include blood pressure, cholesterol, cervical cancer and mammograms among others. Be well.  For more information: https://www.womenshealth.gov/nwhw/
name: Tamsen Fadal
title: National Women's Health Week
